post_text:
Tonight's Regularly scheduled board meeting will be in the UC Library @ 7:00 PM.

Dr. Becky Slothower will begin her first meeting as a UC Tiger with an update from our UC Elem Students on how this year is progressing with COVID changes, all the fun projects we have already engaged in, and upcoming activities. Following we will welcome representatives from the SDE Department of Special Education, Todd Loftin and Tina Spence, to clarify the spec Ed audit findings, process, and expectations moving forward as we strive for excellence in serving ALL UC students.

TOGETHER WE CAN MAKE A DIFFERENCE!

First, we have two pages dedicated to Prom. With the unknown as of now what will happen with Prom, we would like to still dedicate these pages to everyone that was planning on attending the UCHS Prom.

This weekend, April 3rd-April 5th, we are asking that everyone that was planning on attending prom go get in their prom dress or tux and go ahead and have that parent dance that has been a tradition at Union City forever.

PLEASE SHARE THIS

#UCHSpromwithparents

A student is considered chronically absent after missing 10 percent or more of school days. This includes both excused and unexcused absences. Missing 10 percent of school days would be approximately 18 days in a normal 180-day school calendar - just two days per month.

Todd Carel, Supt.

text:
A student is considered chronically absent after missing 10 percent or more of school days. This includes both excused and unexcused absences. Missing 10 percent of school days would be approximately 18 days in a normal 180-day school calendar - just two days per month.

Union City Schools

Union City FFA is with Deana Hoffman Kappus.
May 2, 2019 at 1:31 PM ¬∑

State FFA Convention was a blast this year! We had two students receive recognition for donating a market animal for the Hunger Challenge. This is a program that feeds those who would otherwise go without in our state. Congratulations to Bailey Kappus and Shawna Rodgers and thank you for your contribution!!! We also had 6 seniors receive their State FFA Degree last night. This is more than Union City has ever had in one year!!! Congratulations to Kevin Bornemann, Bailey Kappus, Jennifer Metcalf, Shawna Rodgers, Jamie Schieber, and Jason Schieber!!! And a very special thanks to the students who participated in the courtesy corps, helping to hold doors and assist guests at the convention. Your hard work was greatly appreciated- Rustin Dawson, Preston Shuck, Summer Schneider, and Bryson Skinner.

Recently, UC baseball and softball purchased a new pitching machine. Funds were raised within our own booster accounts. It's an Iron Mike MP6 pitching machine capable of throwing slow-pitch style, fast-pitch style and baseball style. It will hold 600 baseballs and 400 softballs. Thanks to Global Tank and Vessel for loaning us a skytrak to get it upstairs to our indoor hitting facility. Thank you to booster club, students, parents, and coaches for making this possible.

This is the 3rd year Schmidt has taken his students on this trip to experience state of the art equipment, classroom visits, speaking with professors and students, and meeting the Dean. Some of Schmidt's students have gone on to attend OU and pursue a journalism degree. It is really amazing how Coach Schmidt has built this program here at Union City and has had such a positive influence on his students. His program seems to get better every year. Thank you Coach Schmidt!
